    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it still feels like i'm fighting an uphill battle. it feels like there's this hidden force or something eating away at my money before it even hits the principal. is there any way to see exactly how much of my monthly payment is being taken by interest vs the principal in a breakdown?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, absolutely, you can see that breakdown, and it's crucial for understanding your repayment! Your loan statement should provide an \"Amortization Schedule\" or a detailed payment breakdown. This shows exactly how much of your fixed monthly payment is allocated to the interest charge for that period and how much is applied to reduce the actual principal. Seeing those numbers side-by-side is the clearest way to see how much of your payment is being eaten up by the interest. If you don't see it, contact your loan servicer and ask for a detailed amortization schedule.",
      "source": "target",
