    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'll look for the amortization schedule. it just feels like a lot of my money is just disappearing into thin air every month. is there anything else that typically causes the principal to decrease slower than expected, like extra fees or something that might be hiding in the fine print?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the interest calculation is the main culprit, there are a few other things that can make the principal reduction seem slower than you anticipate, though these are usually separate from the core interest calculation. Sometimes, fees like late payment penalties or administrative charges can be added to the balance, which effectively increases the amount you owe, even if your payment is on time. You should meticulously review the fine print for any mention of origination fees or servicing fees that might be added to the principal balance over time. These fees are the hidden things that can make your progress feel slower than it should be.",
      "source": "target",
